title: England v Australia, Rugby World Cup 2019 player ratings: Our verdict on both teams, including who impressed and who struggled
text:
England surged into the Rugby World Cup semi-finals with a thumping win over Australia in Oita.

Jonny May scored two first-half tries to set England on their way, en route to a 40-16 victory.

It is the first time England have reached the final four in 12 years and they will play either New Zealand or Ireland, who face each other in the second quarter-final on Saturday.

But who impressed for England and who struggled most for Australia?

Here are our player ratings for both sides.

England

15. Elliot Daly

Flicked offload to Watson in the build-up to May's first summed up how his distribution has improved. Endured a couple of hesitant moments in the back-field 7
